The paper deals with optimization problems in graphs, specifically the Traveling Salesman Problem and its generalizations. This falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also discusses approximation algorithms and complexity theory, which are relevant to discrete mathematics (cs.DM), game theory (cs.GT), and computational complexity (cs.CC).
